                <header class="major"><h1>MSc Computing Project</h1></header>

                <h2>1. Module Overview</h2>
                <p>The MSc Computing Project is the final major project of the programme. It provides an opportunity to apply research, technical, analytical, and professional skills to a substantial Artificial Intelligence or computing-related problem.</p>

                <h2>2. Learning Outcomes</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Define and investigate a suitable research or development problem.</li>
                    <li>Apply appropriate technical, analytical, and research methods.</li>
                    <li>Critically evaluate project outcomes against objectives and literature.</li>
                    <li>Demonstrate independent learning, project management, and professional practice.</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>3. Artefacts</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Project proposal</li>
                    <li>Literature review</li>
                    <li>Design and methodology documentation</li>
                    <li>Implementation artefacts, code, models, or prototypes</li>
                    <li>Testing, evaluation, and results</li>
                    <li>Final report and reflective evaluation</li>
                </ul>

